  "pdp": {
    "description": "Modern design: Optima 4H combines the best trends in the door industry, including minimalist style, quality materials, and versatile shade. Pure Flush construction will favorably highlight the advantages of the surrounding interior while remaining a self-sufficient and striking element of home design. The distinctive feature of this interior door model is the four horizontal shiny aluminum strips, which form five equal-sized panels on the slab and create an elegant visual effect. Door construction: the door is strong and durable due to a solid pine door frame. Door filling: engineered solid core is an innovative eco-friendly wood fiber material with 12.5 lb/ft³ density. It is responsible for soundproofing and keeping heat inside the room. High-quality finish: the slab is coated with polypropylene (Pecan Nutwood), an environmentally friendly material resistant to moisture and temperature fluctuations. The door with a PP finish is easy to care for, so it is enough to use a damp cloth without aggressive deterge when cleaning. Warranty: 2 years. Frameless Doors Installation Guide - Belldinni Inc In this 7-minute video, you'll find complete instructions on installing frameless doors yourself, from preparing the necessary tools to assembling the door frame, slab, and hardware. We've also collected helpful tips on when to finish the floor and walls. Frameless Doors (Reverse) Installation Guide - Belldinni Inc Clear and step-by-step instructions for assembling and installing Belldinni frameless doors (reverse) are presented in this video. Our specialists share all the relevant information, including the correct renovation sequence. Frame and Wall Painting Guide for Frameless Primed Doors by Belldinni Inc Our experts prepared detailed instructions (6-minute video) that show the entire process, from preparing all the necessary tools to plastering and painting the wall and door.",
